   "source": [
    "# 04. Deep Learning for Demand Forecasting (LSTM)\n",
    "This notebook explores Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks to capture complex temporal dependencies in NYC taxi demand.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Innovations:\n",
    "- **3D Data Reshaping**: Transforming tabular data into [Samples, Time-steps, Features].\n",
    "- **Memory-Efficient Training**: Using `TimeseriesGenerator` to stream data into the GPU/CPU.\n",
    "- **Advanced Evaluation**: Comparing Deep Learning results with our XGBoost baseline."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "d:\\Bon Bon\\SourceCode\\git\\DW-and-DSS-for-Travel-Demand-Predicttion\\.venv\\lib\\site-packages\\google\\api_core\\_python_version_support.py:273: FutureWarning: You are using a Python version (3.10.1) which Google will stop supporting in new releases of google.api_core once it reaches its end of life (2026-10-04). Please upgrade to the latest Python version, or at least Python 3.11, to continue receiving updates for google.api_core past that date.\n",
      "  warnings.warn(message, FutureWarning)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import os\n",
    "from google.cloud import bigquery\n",
    "from dotenv import load_dotenv\n",
    "import tensorflow as tf\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras.layers import LSTM, Dense, Dropout, Input\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.sequence import TimeseriesGenerator\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error\n",
    "\n",
    "load_dotenv('../.env')\n",
    "client = bigquery.Client()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Data Acquisition (BigQuery)\n",
    "We pull the same unified dataset used in XGBoost to ensure a fair comparison."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    # Focus on a specific high-demand zone for LSTM training (e.g., Zone 161)
    df_zone = df[df['pulocation_id'] == 161].copy()
    print(f\"Data points for Zone 161: {len(df_zone)}\")
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Scaling & Pre-processing\n",
    "LSTMs are sensitive to scale. We use `MinMaxScaler` (0-1) for all features."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "scaler = MinMaxScaler()\n",
    "scaled_data = scaler.fit_transform(df_zone[['total_demand', 'hour', 'day_of_week_number']])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Target is the first column (total_demand)\n",
    "y_data = scaled_data[:, 0]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Split Index (Time-based)\n",
    "train_size = int(len(scaled_data) * 0.8)\n",
    "train_data = scaled_data[:train_size]\n",
    "test_data = scaled_data[train_size:]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Creating the Timeseries Generator\n",
    "Instead of creating a massive 3D array in RAM, we use a Generator that provides batches of 24 hours of history to predict the next hour."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "n_input = 24 # Look back 24 hours\n",
    "batch_size = 32\n",
    "\n",
    "train_generator = TimeseriesGenerator(train_data, train_data[:, 0], \n",
    "                                      length=n_input, batch_size=batch_size)\n",
    "\n",
    "test_generator = TimeseriesGenerator(test_data, test_data[:, 0], \n",
    "                                     length=n_input, batch_size=batch_size)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. LSTM Model Architecture\n",
    "A stacked LSTM with Dropout layers to prevent overfitting."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "n_features = train_data.shape[1] # [total_demand, hour, day_of_week]\n",
    "\n",
    "model = Sequential([\n",
    "    Input(shape=(n_input, n_features)),\n",
    "    LSTM(64, activation='relu', return_sequences=True),\n",
    "    Dropout(0.2),\n",
    "    LSTM(32, activation='relu'),\n",
    "    Dense(1)\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='mse')\n",
    "model.summary()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Training with Early Stopping"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "early_stop = tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=5)\n",
    "\n",
    "history = model.fit(train_generator, \n",
    "                    epochs=50, \n",
    "                    validation_data=test_generator, \n",
    "                    callbacks=[early_stop])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Model Persistence\n",
    "Save the Keras model and the Scaler for future inference."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import joblib\n",
    "\n",
    "model.save('../saved_models/lstm/lstm_demand_model_v1.keras')\n",
    "joblib.dump(scaler, '../saved_models/scalers/lstm_scaler.pkl')\n",
    "print(\"LSTM Model and Scaler saved successfully!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Results Visualization"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "predictions = model.predict(test_generator)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Inverse transform to get real trip counts\n",
    "# (Requires dummy columns to match scaler shape)\n",
    "pred_df = pd.DataFrame(np.zeros((len(predictions), n_features)))\n",
    "pred_df[0] = predictions\n",
    "actual_predictions = scaler.inverse_transform(pred_df)[:, 0]\n",
    "\n",
    "actual_values = df_zone['total_demand'].values[train_size + n_input:]\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(14, 5))\n",
    "plt.plot(actual_values[:168], label='Actual Demand')\n",
    "plt.plot(actual_predictions[:168], label='LSTM Forecast', linestyle='--')\n",
    "plt.title(\"LSTM Forecast vs Actual (1 Week Test)\")\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  }
